            ## Reverse
            Velocity.js allows animating back to the previous values using `reverse`. Check the doc [here](http://velocityjs.org/#reverse)

            Simply set `reverse` in the `do` option

            ### Pug
            ```pug
            button.target(
                data-hz-resource='HzAnim',
                data-opt-hz-anim-on='click',
                data-opt-hz-anim-do={"rotateZ":"45deg"}
            ) Rotate
            button(
                data-hz-resource='HzAnim',
                data-opt-hz-anim-on='click',
                data-opt-hz-anim-to='.target',
                data-opt-hz-anim-do='reverse'
            ) Reverse .target
            ```
            ### HTML
            ```html
            <button
                class="target"
                data-hz-resource="HzAnim"
                data-opt-hz-anim-on="click"
                data-opt-hz-anim-do='{"rotateZ":"45deg"}'
            >
                Rotate
            </button>
            <button
                class="target"
                data-hz-resource="HzAnim"
                data-opt-hz-anim-on="click"
                data-opt-hz-anim-to=".target"
                data-opt-hz-anim-do='reverse'
            >
                Reverse .target
            </button>
            ```
        button.target(
            data-hz-resource='HzAnim',
            data-opt-hz-anim-on='click',
            data-opt-hz-anim-do='{"rotateZ":"45deg"}'
        ) Rotate
